main event: A witness observed a green-white object moving rapidly in the sky in St. James, New York on April 21, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 - 5 seconds.,The object was traveling from West to East.,One witness reported no tail while another described an exhaust resembling a comet.,The object was moving at tremendous speed.,The sighting was concluded to be an astronomical event, specifically a meteor.
sighted object: one green-white object in the sky
witness description: a private citizen who lives in St. James, NY
